text:
Hi, I need help with a Custom Workflow Action. I've used this documentation (<https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/api/automation/custom-workflow-actions>) to arrive at my solution, but I'm not able to use the "outputFields" feature

The body of my Custom Workflow Action definition is as follows:

```{
  "actionUrl": "<https://my-domain.xyz/v1/webhooks/HubSpot>",
  "objectTypes": [],
  "published": true,
  "inputFields": [
    {
      "typeDefinition": {
        "name": "campaignId",
        "type": "string",
        "fieldType": "text"
      },
      "supportedValueTypes": [
        "STATIC_VALUE"
      ],
      "isRequired": true
    }
  ],
  "outputFields": [
    {
      "typeDefinition":{
        "name":"couponCode",
        "type":"string",
        "fieldType":"text"
      },
      "supportedValueTypes":[
        "STATIC_VALUE"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "objectRequestOptions": {
    "properties": []
  },
  "labels": {
    "en": {
      "actionName": "Request a Coupon Code",
      "actionDescription": "Request a coupon code for this user",
      "appDisplayName": "Coupon Code",
      "actionCardContent": "Coupon Campaign: {{campaignId}}",
      "inputFieldLabels": {
        "campaignId": "Campaign ID"
      },
      "inputFieldDescriptions": {
        "campaignId": "The Campaign ID to request a coupon code for."
      },
      "outputFieldLabels": {
        "couponCode": "Coupon Code"
      }
    }
  }
}```
`outputFields` and `outputFieldLabels` are both included, and the API request to create the Action succeeds. However, the response body is missing both `outputFields` and `outputFieldLabels`:

```{
  "id": "NNNNNNNN",
  "revisionId": "1",
  "functions": [],
  "actionUrl": "<https://my-domain.xyz/v1/webhooks/HubSpot>",
  "published": true,
  "inputFields": [
    {
      "typeDefinition": {
        "name": "campaignId",
        "type": "string",
        "fieldType": "text",
        "options": [],
        "optionsUrl": null,
        "referencedObjectType": null
      },
      "supportedValueTypes": [
        "STATIC_VALUE"
      ],
      "isRequired": true
    }
  ],
  "objectRequestOptions": {
    "properties": []
  },
  "labels": {
    "en": {
      "inputFieldLabels": {
        "campaignId": "Campaign ID"
      },
      "inputFieldDescriptions": {
        "campaignId": "The Campaign ID to request a coupon code for."
      },
      "actionName": "Request a Coupon Code",
      "actionDescription": "Request a coupon code for this user",
      "appDisplayName": "Coupon Code",
      "actionCardContent": "Coupon Campaign: {{campaignId}}"
    }
  },
  "objectTypes": []
}```
My function completes the workflow action successfully with the following response body:

```{
  "callbackId": "ap-39998554-620951526013-9-0",
  "outputFields": {
    "hs_execution_state": "SUCCESS",
    "couponCode": "2OmiIVfl"
  }
}```
I can see the response body in the workflow's Action Logs; however, I cannot see the Output Field in the workflow action or in the Copy Property action placed after my workflow step.

I've tried creating a new Custom Workflow Action, but I'm still not able to see the Output Field. I've also tried creating a new workflow, but I'm still not able to see the Output Field.

Any help would be appreciated. Thanks!

I've tried two forms for the `outputFields` segment:

```"outputFields": [
    {
      "typeDefinition":{
        "name":"couponCode",
        "type":"string",
        "fieldType":"text"
      },
      "supportedValueTypes":[
        "STATIC_VALUE"
      ]
    }
  ]```
and
```"outputFields": [
    {
      "typeDefinition":{
        "name":"couponCode",
        "type":"string",
        "fieldType":"text"
      }
    }
  ]```
as the documentation is not clear whether `supportedValueTypes` is required.
